<section class="section section--alt" id="qb-cleanup-vs-reconciliation-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who does the work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A Certified ProAdvisor does the cleanup &mdash; and the ongoing reconciliation.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Cleanup and reconciliation aren&rsquo;t an either/or for us &mdash; they&rsquo;re sequential. When a file is behind or broken, a Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor runs the cleanup against a written scope: re-categorizing transactions to the right accounts, removing duplicates without deleting real entries, recovering missing dates, undoing any force-balanced reconciliations, and fixing the chart of accounts &mdash; then reconciling each month, in order, until every period ties to the statement. From there, ongoing reconciliation becomes part of monthly bookkeeping so the file never drifts back. CPA files. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support; an Intuit account, login, or billing matter stays with Intuit.</p>
